sc2AgentCompany.name: sc2AgentCompany
sc2AgentCompany.description: Agent's company name (e.g. Fujitsu Technology Solutions)

sc2AgentBuild.name: sc2AgentBuild
sc2AgentBuild.description: Compilation time and date of agent program

sc2AgentWriteAllowed.name: sc2AgentWriteAllowed
sc2AgentWriteAllowed.description: Defines whether writable objects can be written (except shutdown/power-off operations)

sc2AgentShutdownAllowed.name: sc2AgentShutdownAllowed
sc2AgentShutdownAllowed.description: Defines whether shutdown/power-off objects can be written

sc2LocalServerUnitId.name: sc2LocalServerUnitId
sc2LocalServerUnitId.description: Unit identifier number of the local server (usually is ID 1). This ID can be used as index into the sc2Units table.

sc2NumberUnits.name: sc2NumberUnits
sc2NumberUnits.description: Number of available units (size of sc2Units table).

sc2UnitTable.name: sc2UnitTable
sc2UnitTable.description: Description of all units in this MIB

sc2UnitCabinetNr.name: sc2UnitCabinetNr
sc2UnitCabinetNr.description: Unit cabinet number (used for addressing storage extension cabinets or server blades). The ID of the local server is usually 0.

sc2FrontDoorStatus.name: sc2FrontDoorStatus
sc2FrontDoorStatus.description: Status describing whether the front door is open or closed

sc2HousingOpenStatus.name: sc2HousingOpenStatus
sc2HousingOpenStatus.description: Status describing whether the housing is open or closed

sc2MsgLogLanguages.name: sc2MsgLogLanguages
sc2MsgLogLanguages.description: Supported languages of text message log (comma-seperated list of decimal language codes, see sc2MessageTextLogTable). e.g. '1031,1033' means German and English are supported. English (1033) is the default language and is always available.

sc2UnitWorldWideName.name: sc2UnitWorldWideName
sc2UnitWorldWideName.description: Unit World Wide Name. A 64-bit sized address for storage devices (e.g. '6661E2B0A00B88FB')

sc2RemcsId.name: sc2RemcsId
sc2RemcsId.description: REMCS system identification string (binary data): Format of Fujitsu REMCS ID (40byte) Format = TTMMMMMMMMMMMMmmmmmmmmmmmmCCnnnnnnnnnnnn TT : 2byte : Type ID for Company Name MM...M : 12byte : Model Name mm...m : 12byte : Device Name CC : 2byte : Checksum nn...n : 12byte : Serial number

sc2MsgLogAvailable.name: sc2MsgLogAvailable
sc2MsgLogAvailable.description: Replies whether a message log is available on this unit

sc2ManagementIpAddress.name: sc2ManagementIpAddress
sc2ManagementIpAddress.description: IPv4 address of the server for management purpose with PRIMEQUEST systems only. This is the interface address for managing a server by external management clients when the server has more than one LAN interfaces (represented by an IPv4 address string).

sc2HasUefiFirmware.name: sc2HasUefiFirmware
sc2HasUefiFirmware.description: Replies whether the system is equipped with UEFI firmware

sc2ManagementIpAddressV6.name: sc2ManagementIpAddressV6
sc2ManagementIpAddressV6.description: IPv6 address of the server for management purpose with PRIMEQUEST systems only. This is the interface address for managing a server by external management clients when the server has more than one LAN interfaces (represented by an IPv6 address string).

sc2UnitTableUpdateCount.name: sc2UnitTableUpdateCount
sc2UnitTableUpdateCount.description: Counter defining the update revision of the unit table. This counter is incremented with every table contents change/update.

sc2UnitParentTable.name: sc2UnitParentTable
sc2UnitParentTable.description: Parent-child relationship of all units: list the parent of all available units. Only units that have a parent are listed in this table.

sc2ParentUnit.name: sc2ParentUnit
sc2ParentUnit.description: Unit identifier of this unit's parent

sc2ParentUnitClass.name: sc2ParentUnitClass
sc2ParentUnitClass.description: Parent unit classification (type). This is the same value as in sc2Units table, but can be used for easy class detection.

sc2UnitChildTable.name: sc2UnitChildTable
sc2UnitChildTable.description: Parent-child relationship of all units: list all children of all available units. Only units that have children are listed in this table.

sc2ChildUnitClass.name: sc2ChildUnitClass
sc2ChildUnitClass.description: Unit classification (type). This is the same value as in sc2Units table, but can be used for easy class detection.

sc2ManagementNodeTable.name: sc2ManagementNodeTable
sc2ManagementNodeTable.description: SNMP management node addresses (how to address the units)

sc2UnitNodeName.name: sc2UnitNodeName
sc2UnitNodeName.description: Management node name (DNS name, e.g. apollo.ts.fujitsu.com)

sc2UnitNodeClass.name: sc2UnitNodeClass
sc2UnitNodeClass.description: Management node class: primary: local operating system interface secondary: local management controller LAN interface management-blade: management blade interface (in a blade server chassis) secondary-remote: remote management controller (in an RSB concentrator environment) secondary-remote-backup: backup remote management controller baseboard-controller: local baseboard management controller (BMC)

sc2UnitNodeUseDHCP.name: sc2UnitNodeUseDHCP
sc2UnitNodeUseDHCP.description: Management node uses DHCP to obtain its address

sc2UnitNodeControllerType.name: sc2UnitNodeControllerType
sc2UnitNodeControllerType.description: The type of the remote management controller (for identification), like 'RSB', 'RSB S2', 'RSB S2 LP'... These names will not be changed if defined once.

sc2UnitNodeControllerModel.name: sc2UnitNodeControllerModel
sc2UnitNodeControllerModel.description: The model name of the remote management controller (for displaying), like 'Remote Service Board', 'RemoteView Service Board S2'... This name should not be used for identification, only for displaying (can be changed in different firmware versions)!

sc2UnitNodeControllerFWVersion.name: sc2UnitNodeControllerFWVersion
sc2UnitNodeControllerFWVersion.description: The FW version of the remote management controller

sc2UnitNodeControllerStorage.name: sc2UnitNodeControllerStorage
sc2UnitNodeControllerStorage.description: Status of the controller specific external storage used for the system management.

sc2UnitNodeSNMPEnabled.name: sc2UnitNodeSNMPEnabled
sc2UnitNodeSNMPEnabled.description: SNMP interface is enabled at management node

sc2UnitNodeCIMEnabled.name: sc2UnitNodeCIMEnabled
sc2UnitNodeCIMEnabled.description: CIM protocol is enabled at management node

sc2UnitNodeRemoteIPMIEnabled.name: sc2UnitNodeRemoteIPMIEnabled
sc2UnitNodeRemoteIPMIEnabled.description: Remote IPMI is enabled at management node

sc2NodeTableUpdateCount.name: sc2NodeTableUpdateCount
sc2NodeTableUpdateCount.description: Counter defining the update revision of the management node table. This counter is incremented with every table contents change/update.

sc2ManagementChannelType.name: sc2ManagementChannelType
sc2ManagementChannelType.description: The type of the management channel currently used (this MIB instance).

sc2spBatteryDischargeTime.name: sc2spBatteryDischargeTime
sc2spBatteryDischargeTime.description: Maximum time (in seconds) this backup battery can discharged, after that a shutdown will be performed (-1 = unknown)

sc2spTimeOnBattery.name: sc2spTimeOnBattery
sc2spTimeOnBattery.description: Time (in seconds) the service processor is running on battery since power fail (will be cleared on power recovery)

sc2spDoBatteryChargeCycle.name: sc2spDoBatteryChargeCycle
sc2spDoBatteryChargeCycle.description: Perform a discharge/charge cycle on the backup battery by writing a non-zero value. Reading this object just returns the value 0.

sc2spBatteryChargeLevel.name: sc2spBatteryChargeLevel
sc2spBatteryChargeLevel.description: Reads the current charge level of the rechargeable battery (in percent of the maximum capacity).

sc2ManagedUpsNodeTable.name: sc2ManagedUpsNodeTable
sc2ManagedUpsNodeTable.description: UPS nodes managed by the units

sc2upsMgmtAddress.name: sc2upsMgmtAddress
sc2upsMgmtAddress.description: UPS management interface target address (represented as string; may contain an IP V4 address, IP V6 address or a URL)

sc2upsMibRoot.name: sc2upsMibRoot
sc2upsMibRoot.description: UPS MIB root OID; specifies the root OID of the MIB to be used to query UPS via SNMP (empty string if no SNMP agent available)

sc2upsSnmpCommunity.name: sc2upsSnmpCommunity
sc2upsSnmpCommunity.description: UPS SNMP community name (empty string if no SNMP agent available)

sc2UpsNodeTableUpdateCount.name: sc2UpsNodeTableUpdateCount
sc2UpsNodeTableUpdateCount.description: Counter defining the update revision of the UPS node table. This counter is incremented with every table contents change/update.

sc2ServerTable.name: sc2ServerTable
sc2ServerTable.description: Table containing information about the available servers

sc2srvPhysicalMemory.name: sc2srvPhysicalMemory
sc2srvPhysicalMemory.description: Size of physical main memory installed (MBytes)

sc2srvShutdownCommand.name: sc2srvShutdownCommand
sc2srvShutdownCommand.description: Shutdown the server and switch off or reset; a delay (see object below) can be defined before the command is being executed; when reading that value, always unknown(1) is replied; argument tells what kind of action: power-on: switch power on power-off: switch power off power-cycle: switch power off and switch power on again. shutdown-and-off: execute a shutdown then power off shutdown-and-reset: execute a shutdown then reset shutdown-and-power-cycle: execute a shutdown then power off and on again raise-nmi: raise an NMI (normally causes debugger to start) reset: execute a reset (without shutdown) The value unknown(1) cannot be set.

sc2srvShutdownDelay.name: sc2srvShutdownDelay
sc2srvShutdownDelay.description: Delay time (seconds) the agent waits before executing the shutdown command (see previous command). 0 = immediate action, no delay -1 = unknown (delay not supported) The value unknown(-1) cannot be set.

sc2srvUUID.name: sc2srvUUID
sc2srvUUID.description: Universal Unique ID (UUID) number (as specified in RFC 4122; shown in network byte order, big-endian) - this is a world-wide unique ID number of the server. Can be used for identifying a server. The format is like this: '33221100-5544-7766-8899-AABBCCDDEEFF'

sc2srvPhysicalMemoryOs.name: sc2srvPhysicalMemoryOs
sc2srvPhysicalMemoryOs.description: Size of physical main memory available to the operating system (MBytes). This value is similar to 'sc2srvPhysicalMemory', but may be less if the system has mirror or hot spare memory modules.

sc2srvUUIDWireFormat.name: sc2srvUUIDWireFormat
sc2srvUUIDWireFormat.description: Universal Unique ID (UUID) number (shown in the wire format; little-endian for the first three fields, as consistently used in the PC industry) - this is a world-wide unique ID number of the server. Can be used for identifying a server. The format is like this: '00112233-4455-6677-8899-AABBCCDDEEFF'

sc2srvOsPlatform.name: sc2srvOsPlatform
sc2srvOsPlatform.description: Reports about the current operating system platform (x86, x64)

sc2srvHasEncryptedPartitions.name: sc2srvHasEncryptedPartitions
sc2srvHasEncryptedPartitions.description: Specifies whether encrypted file systems (e.g. by Windows BitLocker) are used (may prevent from BIOS updates)

sc2srvTrustedExecutionTechnologyEnabled.name: sc2srvTrustedExecutionTechnologyEnabled
sc2srvTrustedExecutionTechnologyEnabled.description: Specifies whether Intel Trusted Execution Technology (TXT) is enabled (may prevent from BIOS updates)

sc2LastPowerOffSource.name: sc2LastPowerOffSource
sc2LastPowerOffSource.description: Reason why the system was switched off last time

sc2LastPowerOnSource.name: sc2LastPowerOnSource
sc2LastPowerOnSource.description: Source the system was switched on from

sc2LastPowerOnTime.name: sc2LastPowerOnTime
sc2LastPowerOnTime.description: Time and date (UTC) the system was booted (seconds since 1/1/1970; 0 = unknown or not available)

sc2PowerOnCounts.name: sc2PowerOnCounts
sc2PowerOnCounts.description: Tells how often the server was switched on in its life (0 = unknown or not available)

sc2PowerOnDuration.name: sc2PowerOnDuration
sc2PowerOnDuration.description: Tells how long the system has stayed ON in its life (in seconds; 0 = unknown or not available)

sc2PowerOffDuration.name: sc2PowerOffDuration
sc2PowerOffDuration.description: Tells how long the system has stayed OFF in its life (in seconds; 0 = unknown or not available)

sc2PowerFailRecovery.name: sc2PowerFailRecovery
sc2PowerFailRecovery.description: Action on AC power recovery after AC has failed. not-available(2) : function not available, behavior is hardware-defined. as-before(3) : server gets the same power state as before the AC fail. remain-off(4) : server remains off on power resume. switch-on(5) : server is always switched on on power resume. The value unknown(1) cannot be set, a SET will deliver 'badValue'.

sc2PowerCommand.name: sc2PowerCommand
sc2PowerCommand.description: Switch the unit on or off; mainly used for extension cabinets; argument tells what kind of action: on: switch power on off: switch power off power-cycle: switch power off and switch power on again No graceful system shutdown is performed - use sc2srvShutdownCommand if shutdown of a server is requested! The value unknown(1) cannot be set and will be delivered if the object is read.

sc2PowerSupplyRedundancy.name: sc2PowerSupplyRedundancy
sc2PowerSupplyRedundancy.description: Specifies whether the power supply system contains redundant power supplies and whether redundancy is available

sc2PowerSupplyMatchStatus.name: sc2PowerSupplyMatchStatus
sc2PowerSupplyMatchStatus.description: Status of power supply matching - 'ok' if power supplies do not mismatch

sc2PerformanceTable.name: sc2PerformanceTable
sc2PerformanceTable.description: Server performance and utilisation information (Obsolete! Please use sc2PerformanceValueTable!)

sc2PerformanceType.name: sc2PerformanceType
sc2PerformanceType.description: Server performance object type (description see below)

sc2PerformanceObjectNr.name: sc2PerformanceObjectNr
sc2PerformanceObjectNr.description: Server performance object number (0..n; for types with multiple objects)

sc2PerformanceName.name: sc2PerformanceName
sc2PerformanceName.description: Name (short description) of the performance value (e.g. 'CPU1'). Can be used for displaying a list of performance values in the management frontend.

sc2PerformanceValue.name: sc2PerformanceValue
sc2PerformanceValue.description: Server performance value (value interpretation depending on type; 0xffffffff = unknown): cpu: Load of a single CPU in percent cpu-overall: Overall CPU load in percent pci-load: PCI bus load in percent pci-efficiency: PCI bus efficiency in percent (100% is optimum) pci-transfer: PCI bus transfer rate in MBytes/sec. memory-physical: Physical memory usage in MBytes memory-total: Total memory usage (physical + virtual) in MBytes memory-percent: Physical memory usage in percent

sc2tooDayOfWeek.name: sc2tooDayOfWeek
sc2tooDayOfWeek.description: Day of the week the times should act upon (index); 1=Sunday, 2=Monday...

sc2OnTime.name: sc2OnTime
sc2OnTime.description: Time the system should be switched on (by the real-time clock; in minutes since midnight; -1 = disabled, no on time). Only values -1 and 0..1439 are allowed.

sc2OffTime.name: sc2OffTime
sc2OffTime.description: Time the system should be switched off (by the real-time clock of software; in minutes since midnight; -1 = disabled, no on time). Only values -1 and 0..1439 are allowed.

sc2pmCurrentPowerMonitoringAvailable.name: sc2pmCurrentPowerMonitoringAvailable
sc2pmCurrentPowerMonitoringAvailable.description: Power monitoring and control available on this server: true: Power monitoring and power control is available false: Power monitoring and power control is not available

sc2pmCurrentPowerMonitoringEnabled.name: sc2pmCurrentPowerMonitoringEnabled
sc2pmCurrentPowerMonitoringEnabled.description: Power monitoring enable value: true: Power monitoring and data gathering is enabled false: Power monitoring and data gathering is disabled or not available

sc2pmNominalPowerConsumption.name: sc2pmNominalPowerConsumption
sc2pmNominalPowerConsumption.description: Nominal (maximum) value of the system's power consumption (in Watts; -1 if value not available)

sc2pmCurrentPowerConsumption.name: sc2pmCurrentPowerConsumption
sc2pmCurrentPowerConsumption.description: Current value of the system's power consumption (in Watts; -1 if value not available)

sc2pmCurrentPowerControl.name: sc2pmCurrentPowerControl
sc2pmCurrentPowerControl.description: Power mode control value: disabled: The baseboard management controller does not control the power saving behaviour best-performance: The baseboard management controller gives best performance to the system (power consumption may be increased) minimum-power: The baseboard management controller controls the system in way to consume minimum power (performance may be reduced) automatic: The baseboard management controller automatically controls power consumption between good performance and low power consumption limited: The baseboard management controller controls power consumption by power limit low-noise: The baseboard management controller controls the power to ensure running with lowest noise

sc2pmPowerLimitStatus.name: sc2pmPowerLimitStatus
sc2pmPowerLimitStatus.description: Power limitation status (valid if power control = limited) ok: power consumption is within specified range warning: power consumption is above warning threshold (sc2pmPowerLimitWarning) but below limit error: power consumption is above limit (sc2pmPowerLimitThreshold) disabled: power consumption limiting is disabled

sc2pmPowerLimitThreshold.name: sc2pmPowerLimitThreshold
sc2pmPowerLimitThreshold.description: Maximum limit value of the system's power consumption (in Watts; -1 if value not available; only valid if limiting enabled)

sc2pmPowerLimitWarning.name: sc2pmPowerLimitWarning
sc2pmPowerLimitWarning.description: Warning limit level (in percent of the maximum limit threshold; 0 if value not available; only valid if limiting enabled)

sc2pmRedundancyCritLevel.name: sc2pmRedundancyCritLevel
sc2pmRedundancyCritLevel.description: Upper critical power consumption level (in Watts; -1 if value not available); power supply redundancy lost if level is exceeded

sc2pmPowerControlMode.name: sc2pmPowerControlMode
sc2pmPowerControlMode.description: Configured power control mode value: disabled: The baseboard management controller does not control the power saving behaviour best-performance: The baseboard management controller gives best performance to the system (power consumption may be increased) minimum-power: The baseboard management controller controls the system in way to consume minimum power (performance may be reduced) automatic: The baseboard management controller automatically controls power consumption between good performance and low power consumption scheduled: The baseboard management controller controls power consumption by schedule limited: The baseboard management controller controls power consumption by power limit low-noise: The baseboard management controller controls the power to ensure running with lowest noise

sc2pmPowerDisplayUnit.name: sc2pmPowerDisplayUnit
sc2pmPowerDisplayUnit.description: Configurd unit for the display of power consumption values: Watt: Power consumption values are displayed in Watts Btu/h: Power consumption values are displyed in Btu

sc2UtilizationHistoryTable.name: sc2UtilizationHistoryTable
sc2UtilizationHistoryTable.description: Utilization history table (for power consumption); table only contains existing values (no values for non-existing values)

sc2uthEntity.name: sc2uthEntity
sc2uthEntity.description: Utilization value entity; describes what kind of value to be requested: powerConsumptionDay: power consumption values of the last 24 hours; one value (Watts) per minute powerConsumptionMonth: power consumption values of the last month; one value (Watts) per hour powerConsumptionYear: power consumption values of the last year; one value (Watts) per day

sc2uthTimeStamp.name: sc2uthTimeStamp
sc2uthTimeStamp.description: Time stamp of the currenty history entry (time_t = seconds since 1/1/1970, 0:00 AM as GMT)

sc2uthHardwareUUID.name: sc2uthHardwareUUID
sc2uthHardwareUUID.description: UUID of the hardware instance that delivered the value (from object sc2srvUUID); may change if an installation is migrated to another hardware (e.g. in blade environments)

sc2uthAverageValue.name: sc2uthAverageValue
sc2uthAverageValue.description: Average value (in Watts) within the monitored time period (minute, hour, day)

sc2uthMinValue.name: sc2uthMinValue
sc2uthMinValue.description: Minimum (lowest) value within the monitored time period

sc2uthMaxValue.name: sc2uthMaxValue
sc2uthMaxValue.description: Maximum (highest) value within the monitored time period

sc2psiPowerSourcePhase.name: sc2psiPowerSourcePhase
sc2psiPowerSourcePhase.description: System input phase of power source.

sc2psiPowerSourceVoltage.name: sc2psiPowerSourceVoltage
sc2psiPowerSourceVoltage.description: System nominal input voltage of power source (in Volts; -1 if value not available).

sc2viomCurrentManagerId.name: sc2viomCurrentManagerId
sc2viomCurrentManagerId.description: Identification string of the VIOM manager that currently manages this server

sc2viomEnabled.name: sc2viomEnabled
sc2viomEnabled.description: True if the server is enabled for VIOM

sc2viomBiosSupport.name: sc2viomBiosSupport
sc2viomBiosSupport.description: True if the BIOS supports VIOM

sc2viomConnectionStatus.name: sc2viomConnectionStatus
sc2viomConnectionStatus.description: The connection status for VIOM - bit field: Bit 0 - waiting for VIOM table Bit 1 - waiting for inventory table Bit 2 - waiting for external power-on event

sc2PSRedundancyMode.name: sc2PSRedundancyMode
sc2PSRedundancyMode.description: Configured power supply redundancy mode; configured in Server Configuration

sc2PSRedundancyModeConfig.name: sc2PSRedundancyModeConfig
sc2PSRedundancyModeConfig.description: Configuration of number required power supplies for the different redundancy modes specified in sc2PSRedundancyMode: no-redundancy(2): no redundancy required redundancy-1-1(19): 1 required + 1 spare PSU (psu-redundancy mode) or 1 PSU per AC phase (dual-ac-redundancy mode) redundancy-2-1(35): 2 required + 1 spare PSU (psu-redundancy mode) redundancy-3-1(51): 3 required + 1 spare PSU (psu-redundancy mode) redundancy-2-2(36): 2 PSUs per AC phase (dual-ac-redundancy mode)

sc2PSRedundancyRequiredPowerSupplies.name: sc2PSRedundancyRequiredPowerSupplies
sc2PSRedundancyRequiredPowerSupplies.description: Number of power supplies required for configured redundancy mode

sc2PSRedundancyPopulatedPowerSupplies.name: sc2PSRedundancyPopulatedPowerSupplies
sc2PSRedundancyPopulatedPowerSupplies.description: Number of power supplies populated for configured redundancy mode

sc2PSRedundancyConfigurationStatus.name: sc2PSRedundancyConfigurationStatus
sc2PSRedundancyConfigurationStatus.description: Status of the redundancy configuration; reports the status about whether enough power supplies are installed to operate at the configured redundancy mode

sc2PSRedundancyThresholdStatus.name: sc2PSRedundancyThresholdStatus
sc2PSRedundancyThresholdStatus.description: Status of redundancy threshold; reports the status about whether the actual power consumption exceeds the maximum power consumption level for the configured redundancy mode.

sc2PSRedundancyStatus.name: sc2PSRedundancyStatus
sc2PSRedundancyStatus.description: Status of power supply redundancy; similar to sc2PowerSupplyRedundancy, but with additional status evaluation according to the power supply redundancy configuration. not-available(2): redundancy not required and not available (no error) ok(3): redundancy required and available warning(4): redundancy required but not available error(5): redundancy required but severe problem detected

sc2PerfValUnitId.name: sc2PerfValUnitId
sc2PerfValUnitId.description: Unit identifier (index, 1..n). For performacne values on local system use 1!

sc2PerfValType.name: sc2PerfValType
sc2PerfValType.description: Server performance object type (description see below)

sc2PerfValObjectNr.name: sc2PerfValObjectNr
sc2PerfValObjectNr.description: Server performance object number (1..n; for types with multiple objects)

sc2PerfValName.name: sc2PerfValName
sc2PerfValName.description: Name (short description) of the performance value (e.g. 'CPU1'). Can be used for displaying a list of performance values in the management frontend.

sc2PerfValCurrentValue.name: sc2PerfValCurrentValue
sc2PerfValCurrentValue.description: Server performance value (value interpretation depending on type; 0xffffffff = unknown): physicalMemoryUsageMb: Physical memory usage in MBytes physicalMemoryUsagePercent: Physical memory usage in percent totalMemoryUsageMb: Total memory usage (physical + virtual) in MBytes totalMemoryUsagePercent: Total memory usage (physical + virtual) in percent overallCpuUsagePercent: Overall CPU load in percent logicalCpuUsagePercent: Load of a single CPU in percent

sc2tempCurrentTemperature.name: sc2tempCurrentTemperature
sc2tempCurrentTemperature.description: Current temperature at this sensor (degrees Celsius; 0 if unknown or sensor failed)

sc2tempWarningLevel.name: sc2tempWarningLevel
sc2tempWarningLevel.description: Maximum temperature - warning level (degrees Celsius; 0 if unknown or undefined)

sc2tempCriticalLevel.name: sc2tempCriticalLevel
sc2tempCriticalLevel.description: Maximum temperature - critical level (degrees Celsius; 0 if unknown or undefined), system shutdown may occur if this level is exceeded

sc2tempCriticalReaction.name: sc2tempCriticalReaction
sc2tempCriticalReaction.description: Reaction if temperature exceeds the critical level (the value unknown(1) cannot be set)

sc2fanCurrentSpeed.name: sc2fanCurrentSpeed
sc2fanCurrentSpeed.description: Current cooling device speed (revolutions per minute; 0 if unknown or failed)

sc2fanQuality.name: sc2fanQuality
sc2fanQuality.description: Quality of cooling device (in percent of nominal speed - measured at full speed)

sc2fanFailReaction.name: sc2fanFailReaction
sc2fanFailReaction.description: Reaction if the cooling device fails (the value unknown(1) cannot be set)

sc2fanFailShutdownDelay.name: sc2fanFailShutdownDelay
sc2fanFailShutdownDelay.description: Delay time (in seconds) when shutdown should commit on cooling device fail (if shutdown-and-off is configured; 0 = immediately, -1 = unknown, cannot be set)

sc2fanCoolingDeviceType.name: sc2fanCoolingDeviceType
sc2fanCoolingDeviceType.description: Type of cooling device (whether fan or liquid cooling pump) fan(2): fan liquid(3): liquid cooling pump

sc2afExhaustAirflowVolume.name: sc2afExhaustAirflowVolume
sc2afExhaustAirflowVolume.description: System exhaust airflow volume ('-1' if value not available)

sc2SystemBoardProductNumber.name: sc2SystemBoardProductNumber
sc2SystemBoardProductNumber.description: Product number (may be identical to ModelName)

sc2SystemBoardSerialNumber.name: sc2SystemBoardSerialNumber
sc2SystemBoardSerialNumber.description: Serial number (not available for all boards)

sc2SystemBoardDesignation.name: sc2SystemBoardDesignation
sc2SystemBoardDesignation.description: Designation (important when multiple system boards are available)

sc2SystemBoardSDCardSlotPresent.name: sc2SystemBoardSDCardSlotPresent
sc2SystemBoardSDCardSlotPresent.description: System board contains SD card slot

sc2psPowerSupplyLoad.name: sc2psPowerSupplyLoad
sc2psPowerSupplyLoad.description: Actual power supply output load in Watts (0 = not available)

sc2psPowerSupplyNominal.name: sc2psPowerSupplyNominal
sc2psPowerSupplyNominal.description: Nominal power supply output load in Watts (0 = not available), the maximum value the power supply can provide

sc2VoltageTable.name: sc2VoltageTable
sc2VoltageTable.description: Voltages - all voltage values are in 1/100th Volts; a value of 330 means 3.30 Volts (0xffffffff = unknown)

sc2VoltageStatus.name: sc2VoltageStatus
sc2VoltageStatus.description: Voltage status not-available(2): no voltage available (e.g. CPU voltage on empty CPU socket) ok(3): voltage value is in normal range too-low(4): voltage value is below nominal range too-high(5): voltage value is above upper limit out-of-range(6): voltage value is out of normal range (cannot detect whether too low or too high) warning(7): voltage warning (e.g. battery failure predicted)

sc2VoltageCurrentValue.name: sc2VoltageCurrentValue
sc2VoltageCurrentValue.description: Voltage current value (in mV; 0xFFFFFFFF = unknown; negative voltages are reported as negative values: -1770 (0xFFFFF916) means -1.77 Volts)

sc2VoltageNominalValue.name: sc2VoltageNominalValue
sc2VoltageNominalValue.description: Voltage nominal value (in mV; -1 = unknown; negative voltages are reported as negative values)

sc2VoltageMinimumLevel.name: sc2VoltageMinimumLevel
sc2VoltageMinimumLevel.description: Voltage minimum level (in mV; -1 = unknown; negative voltages are reported as negative values)

sc2VoltageMaximumLevel.name: sc2VoltageMaximumLevel
sc2VoltageMaximumLevel.description: Voltage maximum level (in mV; -1 = unknown; negative voltages are reported as negative values)

sc2VoltageCurrentLoad.name: sc2VoltageCurrentLoad
sc2VoltageCurrentLoad.description: Current output load on this voltage line, in percent of the maximum load (0xFFFFFFFF = unknown)

sc2cpuStatus.name: sc2cpuStatus
sc2cpuStatus.description: CPU status: unknown(1): CPU status could not be evaluated not-present(2): CPU socket is empty ok(3): CPU is available and working properly disabled(4): CPU was manually disabled in BIOS setup error(5): CPU has encountered errors but is still in use failed(6): CPU has failed and is disabled missing-termination(7): CPU socket needs a terminator module when not populated but the terminator is missing prefailure-warning(8): CPU has encountered too many correctable errors within a certain time period and is predicted to fail in near future

sc2cpuCurrentSpeed.name: sc2cpuCurrentSpeed
sc2cpuCurrentSpeed.description: CPU speed (frequency in MHz, -1 if unknown)

sc2cpuNumberLogicals.name: sc2cpuNumberLogicals
sc2cpuNumberLogicals.description: Number of (physically available) logical CPUs within one physical CPU (for hyper-threading and multi-core CPUs). This is the sum of all cores and all logical CPUs of a hyper-threading CPU, -1 if unknown or not available.

sc2cpuCacheL1Size.name: sc2cpuCacheL1Size
sc2cpuCacheL1Size.description: Size of first level cache (in kBytes, 0 if unknown or not available)

sc2cpuCacheL2Size.name: sc2cpuCacheL2Size
sc2cpuCacheL2Size.description: Size of second level cache (in kBytes, 0 if unknown or not available)

sc2cpuCacheL3Size.name: sc2cpuCacheL3Size
sc2cpuCacheL3Size.description: Size of third level cache (in kBytes, 0 if unknown or not available)

sc2cpuNumberCores.name: sc2cpuNumberCores
sc2cpuNumberCores.description: Number of (physically available) cores within one physical CPU (for multi-core CPUs, platform dependent), 0 if unknown or not available

sc2cpuFamily.name: sc2cpuFamily
sc2cpuFamily.description: CPU family code. This enumerated value is specified by the DMTF SMBIOS specification (processor information, type 4).

sc2cpuEnabledCores.name: sc2cpuEnabledCores
sc2cpuEnabledCores.description: Number of effectively enabled cores within one physical CPU (for multi-core CPUs; 0 if unknown)

sc2cpuConfigurationStatus.name: sc2cpuConfigurationStatus
sc2cpuConfigurationStatus.description: CPU configuration status: unknown(1): CPU status could not be evaluated normal(2): Regular CPU configuration disabledManually(3): CPU was manually disabled (in BIOS setup) hotSpare(4): CPU is a hot-spare CPU (for future use) mirror(5): CPU is mirrored (for future use) notUsable(7): CPU is currently not usable (due to configuration problems) configurationError(8): CPU misconfiguration

sc2cpuMCDRAMSize.name: sc2cpuMCDRAMSize
sc2cpuMCDRAMSize.description: Size of the onboard MCDRAM (GByte; 0 if no MCDRAM is available)

sc2cpuMCDRAMSpeed.name: sc2cpuMCDRAMSpeed
sc2cpuMCDRAMSpeed.description: Speed of the onboard MCDRAM (MT/s; 0 if no MCDRAM is available)

sc2cpuMCDRAMMode.name: sc2cpuMCDRAMMode
sc2cpuMCDRAMMode.description: Operation mode of the onboard MCDRAM: undefined(1): Mode is not defined (no MCDRAM available) flat(2): MCDRAM is used as standalone memory exclusively or in addition to external RAM cache(3): MCDRAM is used as a cache for external RAM hybrid(3): Part of MCDRAM is used as a cache, rest as standalone memory (see sc2cpuMCDRAMCacheSize)

sc2cpuMCDRAMCacheSize.name: sc2cpuMCDRAMCacheSize
sc2cpuMCDRAMCacheSize.description: Portion of the onboard MCDRAM used as a cache in hybrid mode (in percent; 0 if no MCDRAM is available or other mode than hybrid)

sc2cpuMCDRAMMemoryModel.name: sc2cpuMCDRAMMemoryModel
sc2cpuMCDRAMMemoryModel.description: Memory model of the onboard MCDRAM: undefined(1): Model is not defined (no MCDRAM available) all2all(2): All2All subNumaCluster2(3): Sub NUMA Cluster - 2 subNumaCluster4(4): Sub NUMA Cluster - 4 hemisphere(5): Hemisphere mode quadrant(6): Quadrant mode

sc2memModuleStatus.name: sc2memModuleStatus
sc2memModuleStatus.description: Memory module status: unknown(1): Module status could not be evaluated not-present(2): Module socket is empty ok(3): Module is available and working properly disabled(4): Module was manually disabled in BIOS setup error(5): Module has encountered errors but is still in use failed(6): Module has failed and was disabled prefailure-predicted(7): Module has encountered too many correctable errors within a certain time period and is predicted to fail in near future hidden(11): Module socket is not available and should be hidden

sc2memModuleBank.name: sc2memModuleBank
sc2memModuleBank.description: Memory module bank number (-1 if unknown) Due to the fact that modern mainboards do no longer have fixed banks, this value is OBSOLETE!

sc2memModuleCapacity.name: sc2memModuleCapacity
sc2memModuleCapacity.description: Memory module size (capacity in MBytes; -1 if unknown)

sc2memModuleStartAddress.name: sc2memModuleStartAddress
sc2memModuleStartAddress.description: Memory module start address (in MBytes; -1 if unknown) Due to the fact that modern mainboards do no longer show start addresses, this value is OBSOLETE!

sc2memModuleType.name: sc2memModuleType
sc2memModuleType.description: Memory module type (SDRAM, DDRAM, DDR2, DDR3, ...)

sc2memModuleCorrErrors.name: sc2memModuleCorrErrors
sc2memModuleCorrErrors.description: Number of memory module correctable errors (-1 if unknown)

sc2memModuleUncorrErrors.name: sc2memModuleUncorrErrors
sc2memModuleUncorrErrors.description: Number of memory module uncorrectable errors (-1 if unknown)

sc2memModuleApproved.name: sc2memModuleApproved
sc2memModuleApproved.description: Memory module approved for this machine

sc2memModuleConfiguration.name: sc2memModuleConfiguration
sc2memModuleConfiguration.description: Memory module configuration: unknown(1): Module configuration could not be evaluated normal(2): Module is in normal non-redundant configuration or slot is empty disabled(3): Module is disabled (manually through BIOS setup) hotSpare(4): Module is a hot-spare (standby) module, which will be used as a run-time-replacement for failed modules mirror(5): Module is part of a mirror configuration raid(6): Module is part of a RAID configuration notUsable(7): Module is not usable in the actual configuration because of architectural restrictions configurationError(8): Module is not active due to memory misconfiguration This object replaces the previous redundancy status values hot-spare and mirror in sc2memModuleStatus.

sc2memModuleFrequency.name: sc2memModuleFrequency
sc2memModuleFrequency.description: Memory module actual front side bus frequency (in MHz; -1 if unknown). This value is based on the BIOS settings

sc2memModuleMaxFrequency.name: sc2memModuleMaxFrequency
sc2memModuleMaxFrequency.description: Memory module maximum front side bus frequency (in MHz; -1 if unknown). This value is based on memory module SPD data

sc2memModuleVoltInterface.name: sc2memModuleVoltInterface
sc2memModuleVoltInterface.description: Memory module interface voltage interface description

sc2cpuMultithreadEnable.name: sc2cpuMultithreadEnable
sc2cpuMultithreadEnable.description: Multithreading of CPU enabled This object is OBSOLETE for future implementations; use object 'sc2cpuMultithreadingEnabled' from 'sc2CPUTable' instead!

sc2ComponentPowerConsumptionTable.name: sc2ComponentPowerConsumptionTable
sc2ComponentPowerConsumptionTable.description: Table of component power consumption data

sc2cpcComponentClass.name: sc2cpcComponentClass
sc2cpcComponentClass.description: Component class enumeration (based on IPMI v1.0 entity ID)

sc2cpcCurrentValue.name: sc2cpcCurrentValue
sc2cpcCurrentValue.description: Current component power consumption in Watts

sc2TrustedPlatformModuleTable.name: sc2TrustedPlatformModuleTable
sc2TrustedPlatformModuleTable.description: Trusted Platform Module (TPM) status information (see corresponding TPM specification for detailed description of these states)

sc2tpmHardwareAvailable.name: sc2tpmHardwareAvailable
sc2tpmHardwareAvailable.description: TPM hardware is available ('unknown' if hardware availability cannot be detected; no interface found)

sc2tpmBiosEnabled.name: sc2tpmBiosEnabled
sc2tpmBiosEnabled.description: TPM hardware is enabled by BIOS ('unknown' if hardware is not available; a reboot is required to change this value)

sc2tpmEnabled.name: sc2tpmEnabled
sc2tpmEnabled.description: TPM is enabled (by software; cannot take ownership if disabled; 'unknown' if hardware is not available or disabled)

sc2tpmActivated.name: sc2tpmActivated
sc2tpmActivated.description: TPM is activated (by software; 'unknown' if hardware is not available or disabled)

sc2tpmOwnership.name: sc2tpmOwnership
sc2tpmOwnership.description: TPM ownership is established (valid endorsement key is existing; 'unknown' if hardware is not available or disabled)

sc2PersistentMemoryModuleTable.name: sc2PersistentMemoryModuleTable
sc2PersistentMemoryModuleTable.description: Additional information about persistent (non-volatile) memory modules to extend the sc2MemoryModuleTable. This table uses the index numbers of the previous sc2MemoryModuleTable, but only contains rows where a persistent DIMM module is detected.

sc2nvmemPackageSparingCapable.name: sc2nvmemPackageSparingCapable
sc2nvmemPackageSparingCapable.description: Module is capable of providing spare memory

sc2nvmemTotalSize.name: sc2nvmemTotalSize
sc2nvmemTotalSize.description: Total size of memory module (in GBytes; including reserved spare space)

sc2nvmemRawCapacity.name: sc2nvmemRawCapacity
sc2nvmemRawCapacity.description: Maximum capacity that can be allocated for use in any of the supported modes (in GBytes; excluding reserved space)

sc2nvmemVolatilePercent.name: sc2nvmemVolatilePercent
sc2nvmemVolatilePercent.description: Capacity of volatile memory (in percent of total size)

sc2nvmemPersistentPercent.name: sc2nvmemPersistentPercent
sc2nvmemPersistentPercent.description: Capacity of persistent memory (in percent of total size)

sc2nvmemVolatileStart.name: sc2nvmemVolatileStart
sc2nvmemVolatileStart.description: Start address of the volatile memory region

sc2nvmemPersistentStart.name: sc2nvmemPersistentStart
sc2nvmemPersistentStart.description: Start address of the persistent memory region

sc2nvmemHealthStatusFatal.name: sc2nvmemHealthStatusFatal
sc2nvmemHealthStatusFatal.description: Fatal error status (data loss has occurred or is imminent)

sc2nvmemPowerOnTime.name: sc2nvmemPowerOnTime
sc2nvmemPowerOnTime.description: Lifetime the DIMM has been powered on (in seconds)

sc2nvmemUpTime.name: sc2nvmemUpTime
sc2nvmemUpTime.description: Current uptime of the DIMM for the current power cycle (in seconds)

sc2msgLogEntryData.name: sc2msgLogEntryData
sc2msgLogEntryData.description: Message log entry data (binary; one message per table entry)

sc2WatchdogTime.name: sc2WatchdogTime
sc2WatchdogTime.description: Watchdog timeout period in seconds (-1 = unknown)

sc2WatchdogAction.name: sc2WatchdogAction
sc2WatchdogAction.description: Watchdog timeout action; the value unknown(1) can't be written. Not all watchdog type allow setting all of the values (-> BADVALUE).

sc2RecoverySettingTable.name: sc2RecoverySettingTable
sc2RecoverySettingTable.description: ASR&R (Automatic server recovery and restart) settings

sc2asrNrRebootRetries.name: sc2asrNrRebootRetries
sc2asrNrRebootRetries.description: Current number of retries to reboot/restart the server when a failure shutdown (and power-off) had occured. After this number of retries the action defined in 'sc2asrRebootFailAction' will be executed (-1 = unknown, no retries).

sc2asrDefaultRebootRetries.name: sc2asrDefaultRebootRetries
sc2asrDefaultRebootRetries.description: Default number of retries for server failure reboot. The above object 'sc2asrNrRebootRetries' will be set to this value after the server is working properly for a certain amount of time.

sc2asrNextBootSource.name: sc2asrNextBootSource
sc2asrNextBootSource.description: Source medium to boot from (next time): operating-system: boot from floppy or hard disk diag-system: boot from alternate diagnostic system (only for SCSI systems, load diagnostic system from alternate IDE disk). remote-disk: boot from remote network disk

sc2asrRebootFailAction.name: sc2asrRebootFailAction
sc2asrRebootFailAction.description: Specifies the action after a specified number of failed reboot retries (the object 'sc2asrNrRebootRetries' has reached zero). The value no-diag-system(4) means that a diagnostics system is not available.

sc2asrRestartDelay.name: sc2asrRestartDelay
sc2asrRestartDelay.description: Delay (in minutes) after that the system should be automatically switched on again (by real-time clock) after an error power-off. Setting this value to zero means immediate restart (power-cycle only). Automatic restart may be disabled by setting the 'sc2asrRebootFailAction' to 'switch-off' and the 'sc2asrDefaultRebootRetries' to zero.

sc2asrPostErrorHalt.name: sc2asrPostErrorHalt
sc2asrPostErrorHalt.description: Describes what to do when a POST error has occured (halt on any error, no halt on any error...).

sc2MessageTextLogTable.name: sc2MessageTextLogTable
sc2MessageTextLogTable.description: Error and event message handling, reported as text strings

sc2msgTextLogLanguage.name: sc2msgTextLogLanguage
sc2msgTextLogLanguage.description: Message log entry language (index, Windows language code) e.g. 1031, 1033 for German, English (default; always available)

sc2msgTextLogTimestamp.name: sc2msgTextLogTimestamp
sc2msgTextLogTimestamp.description: Message log entry time stamp (time_t = seconds since 1/1/1970, 0:00 AM as GMT)

sc2msgTextLogMessage.name: sc2msgTextLogMessage
sc2msgTextLogMessage.description: Message log entry message string (multi-byte string; multi-language; not every language may be implemented)

sc2msgTextLogCSSComponent.name: sc2msgTextLogCSSComponent
sc2msgTextLogCSSComponent.description: Component which caused the log message may be replaced by the customer (CSS=Customer Self Service)

sc2MessageLogActionHintTable.name: sc2MessageLogActionHintTable
sc2MessageLogActionHintTable.description: Action text strings for error and event messages

sc2mlaLanguage.name: sc2mlaLanguage
sc2mlaLanguage.description: Action text language (index, Windows language code) e.g. 1031, 1033 for German, English

sc2AgentStatus.name: sc2AgentStatus
sc2AgentStatus.description: Overall status of all monitored components in this agent ok(1): all components are working properly; no warnings, no errors warning(2): at least one component reports a warning status or a redundant component reports an error status error(3): at least one non-redundant component reports an error status unknown(5): none of the components has a valid status (e.g. during initialization) notPresent(6): none of the components is present notManageable(7): none of the components is manageable

sc2StatusComponentTable.name: sc2StatusComponentTable
sc2StatusComponentTable.description: Table with status values of the components in this agent. The table summarizes all instances of one component to one status value.

sc2csStatusOverall.name: sc2csStatusOverall
sc2csStatusOverall.description: Overall status (worst status of all components) in this unit

sc2csStatusBoot.name: sc2csStatusBoot
sc2csStatusBoot.description: Boot status (errors from power-on selftest and boot)

sc2ComponentStatusSensorTable.name: sc2ComponentStatusSensorTable
sc2ComponentStatusSensorTable.description: This table contains the component status sensor table of the BMC (baseboard management controller). Additionally it also holds the CSS (Customer Self Service) information.

sc2cssSensorDevice.name: sc2cssSensorDevice
sc2cssSensorDevice.description: Name of device (entity) the component status sensor belongs to

sc2cssSensorDeviceInstance.name: sc2cssSensorDeviceInstance
sc2cssSensorDeviceInstance.description: Instance number of device (entity) the component status sensor belongs to

sc2cssSensorPhysicalLed.name: sc2cssSensorPhysicalLed
sc2cssSensorPhysicalLed.description: If set, component has a physical status LED showing the sensor status

sc2cssSensorCssComponent.name: sc2cssSensorCssComponent
sc2cssSensorCssComponent.description: If set, component may be replaced by the customer (CSS 'custormer-self-service' component)

sc2cssSensorStatus.name: sc2cssSensorStatus
sc2cssSensorStatus.description: Status returned by the component status sensor

sc2cssComponentServicePartId.name: sc2cssComponentServicePartId
sc2cssComponentServicePartId.description: Spare part number of the replaceable component; used to create a link to the spare part list on the service's spare part catalogue. This usually is the component's designation string, with blanks substituted by underscores.

sc2cssTableSize.name: sc2cssTableSize
sc2cssTableSize.description: Number of entries in the component status sensor table

sc2MaintenanceObjectTable.name: sc2MaintenanceObjectTable
sc2MaintenanceObjectTable.description: Table containing some other maintenance objects

sc2ErrorCounterStartTime.name: sc2ErrorCounterStartTime
sc2ErrorCounterStartTime.description: Memory module error counter start time (seconds since 1/1/1970, -1 if unknown). This is the time when the error counters were started or reset last time.

sc2SendTestTrap.name: sc2SendTestTrap
sc2SendTestTrap.description: Send a test trap (test alarm) to the manager application(s) to test connection and trap configuration; trap cannot be disabled. Initiate test trap sending by writing a non-zero value. Reading this object just returns the value 0.

sc2AddTrapDestination.name: sc2AddTrapDestination
sc2AddTrapDestination.description: Add the specified IP address (of the management station) to the trap destination list of this server. That client will become an alarm receiver for traps of this server.

sc2DeployInfoTable.name: sc2DeployInfoTable
sc2DeployInfoTable.description: Table with data of deployment information. This table is OBSOLETE (no longer used for new implementations)!

sc2DeployInfoMasterImageReference.name: sc2DeployInfoMasterImageReference
sc2DeployInfoMasterImageReference.description: URL in UNC notification (but in ASCII) to remote image file (with the extensions of *.img, *.cfg, *.txt)

sc2DeployInfoStatusOfBlade.name: sc2DeployInfoStatusOfBlade
sc2DeployInfoStatusOfBlade.description: Status of this server: power-down(2): waiting for boot standby(3): power management mode system-boot-failure(4): system boot failure bios-setup(5): BIOS setup or boot phase booting(6): ACPI OS currently booting

sc2DeployInfoLanStatusOfSlot.name: sc2DeployInfoLanStatusOfSlot
sc2DeployInfoLanStatusOfSlot.description: Defines wether the IP-LAN definitions are valid or not.

sc2DeployInfoAutomaticRecovery.name: sc2DeployInfoAutomaticRecovery
sc2DeployInfoAutomaticRecovery.description: Defines if this server blade should be provided automatic recovery.

sc2DeployInfoBootMode.name: sc2DeployInfoBootMode
sc2DeployInfoBootMode.description: Boot mode of the server for remote deployment: normal(2): boot from standard disk subsystem pxeBiosSetup(3): boot from PXE according to BIOS setup settings (for OEM systems) pxeLanx(y): boot from PXE LAN interface x (0..3)

sc2OemDeployInfoTable.name: sc2OemDeployInfoTable
sc2OemDeployInfoTable.description: Table with data of server OEM information. This table is OBSOLETE (no longer used for new implementations)!

sc2DeployLanInterfaceTable.name: sc2DeployLanInterfaceTable
sc2DeployLanInterfaceTable.description: Table with system LAN interfaces information: This table lists all real LAN interfaces in same physical order as the BIOS uses it for PXE boot. Only on-board interfaces are listed; no virtual interfaces.

sc2DriverMonitorComponentTable.name: sc2DriverMonitorComponentTable
sc2DriverMonitorComponentTable.description: Table of components monitored by the driver monitor. Foreign index sc2uUnitId is from sc2UnitTable.

sc2drvmonCompIndex.name: sc2drvmonCompIndex
sc2drvmonCompIndex.description: Component index (index, 1..n). This is an index over all component classes, but unit specific.

sc2drvmonCompName.name: sc2drvmonCompName
sc2drvmonCompName.description: Name or designation of the component

sc2drvmonCompDriverName.name: sc2drvmonCompDriverName
sc2drvmonCompDriverName.description: Name of the driver that created the event record

sc2drvmonCompLocationDesignation.name: sc2drvmonCompLocationDesignation
sc2drvmonCompLocationDesignation.description: Device location designation (if it is an adapter or other hardware component); e.g. 'PCI Slot #2' or 'IOB#1-FUNC#0'

sc2drvmonCompLocationKey.name: sc2drvmonCompLocationKey
sc2drvmonCompLocationKey.description: Device location key, used for identifying the component in other tables (like PCI device table); e.g. 'TYPE_PCI&BUS_3&DEV_14&FUNC_0'

sc2drvmonCompStatus.name: sc2drvmonCompStatus
sc2drvmonCompStatus.description: Status of the component; caused by specific error events, reset by corresponding 'component OK' events or by manual acknowledge

sc2drvmonCompErrorAcknowledge.name: sc2drvmonCompErrorAcknowledge
sc2drvmonCompErrorAcknowledge.description: Acknowledge an error condition (reset error or warning status) of the component by writing a non-zero value (reading this object just returns the value 0)

sc2DriverMonitorMessageTable.name: sc2DriverMonitorMessageTable
sc2DriverMonitorMessageTable.description: Table of messages gathered by the driver monitor. The messages are based on the monitored operating system event log and are available in translated languages. Foreign indexes: sc2uUnitId is from sc2UnitTable, sc2msgTextLogLanguage from sc2MessageTextLogTable, sc2drvmonCompClass, sc2drvmonCompType and sc2drvmonCompIndex from sc2DriverMonitorComponentTable. When sc2drvmonCompIndex is 0, the event could not be assigned to any component.

sc2drvmonMsgTimestamp.name: sc2drvmonMsgTimestamp
sc2drvmonMsgTimestamp.description: Driver message entry time stamp (time_t = seconds since 1/1/1970, 0:00 AM as GMT)

sc2drvmonMsgMessage.name: sc2drvmonMsgMessage
sc2drvmonMsgMessage.description: Message entry string (multi-language; not every language may be implemented, then English message has to be requested)

sc2drvmonMsgEventId.name: sc2drvmonMsgEventId
sc2drvmonMsgEventId.description: Message entry error code (this code is a driver monitor specific error code)

sc2drvmonMsgSeverity.name: sc2drvmonMsgSeverity
sc2drvmonMsgSeverity.description: Message entry severity (may be different from original event log severity)

sc2drvmonMsgErrorCode.name: sc2drvmonMsgErrorCode
sc2drvmonMsgErrorCode.description: Message entry error code (must be used to get summary, causes and resolutions from sc2MessageLogActionHintTable table)

sc2drvmonOrigLogMessage.name: sc2drvmonOrigLogMessage
sc2drvmonOrigLogMessage.description: Original operating system event log / syslog entry message (only available in the server's original language or in english, depending on the driver that created that entry)

sc2drvmonOrigLogId.name: sc2drvmonOrigLogId
sc2drvmonOrigLogId.description: Original log entry ID number (may not be available for some platforms/controllers, then ID = 0)

sc2drvmonTableUpdateCount.name: sc2drvmonTableUpdateCount
sc2drvmonTableUpdateCount.description: Counter defining the update revision of the driver monitoring tables. This counter is incremented with every change/update of the driver monitoring tables.

sc2TrapInfoServerName.name: sc2TrapInfoServerName
sc2TrapInfoServerName.description: Name of the server the trap comes from

sc2TrapInfoTime.name: sc2TrapInfoTime
sc2TrapInfoTime.description: Time when the trap occured (in seconds since 01/01/1970 00:00h)

sc2TrapInfoObjectDesignation.name: sc2TrapInfoObjectDesignation
sc2TrapInfoObjectDesignation.description: Designation string for object that generated the trap (fan, temperature sensor...)

sc2TrapInfoString.name: sc2TrapInfoString
sc2TrapInfoString.description: Additional string to be displayed in the trap text

sc2TrapInfoInteger.name: sc2TrapInfoInteger
sc2TrapInfoInteger.description: Additional number to be displayed in the trap text

sc2TrapInfoInteger2.name: sc2TrapInfoInteger2
sc2TrapInfoInteger2.description: Additional number to be displayed in the trap text

sc2TrapTest.name: sc2TrapTest
sc2TrapTest.description: Test trap to verify trap connection.

sc2TrapCommunicationFailure.name: sc2TrapCommunicationFailure
sc2TrapCommunicationFailure.description: The communication with management controller failed!

sc2TrapCommunicationEstablished.name: sc2TrapCommunicationEstablished
sc2TrapCommunicationEstablished.description: The communication with the management controller was reestablished

sc2TrapBiosSelftestError.name: sc2TrapBiosSelftestError
sc2TrapBiosSelftestError.description: A critical error happend while BIOS selftest. This error needs to be acknowledged to clear the error condition.

sc2TrapSevereSystemError.name: sc2TrapSevereSystemError
sc2TrapSevereSystemError.description: The system was restarted after a severe problem. See server management message log (recovery log) for detailed information.

sc2TrapFanAdded.name: sc2TrapFanAdded
sc2TrapFanAdded.description: The indicated hot-plug fan or liquid pump was inserted.

sc2TrapFanRemoved.name: sc2TrapFanRemoved
sc2TrapFanRemoved.description: The indicated hot-plug fan or liquid pump was removed.

sc2TrapFanOk.name: sc2TrapFanOk
sc2TrapFanOk.description: The indicated fan or liquid pump is working again.

sc2TrapFanCritical.name: sc2TrapFanCritical
sc2TrapFanCritical.description: The indicated fan or liquid pump became critical

sc2TrapFanFailed.name: sc2TrapFanFailed
sc2TrapFanFailed.description: The indicated fan or liquid pump failed.

sc2TrapRedundantFanFailed.name: sc2TrapRedundantFanFailed
sc2TrapRedundantFanFailed.description: The indicated redundant fan or liquid pump failed

sc2TrapTempOk.name: sc2TrapTempOk
sc2TrapTempOk.description: The temperature of the indicated sensor has decreased to the normal level.

sc2TrapTempWarning.name: sc2TrapTempWarning
sc2TrapTempWarning.description: The temperature of the indicated sensor has reached the warning level.

sc2TrapTempCritical.name: sc2TrapTempCritical
sc2TrapTempCritical.description: The temperature of the indicated sensor is out of tolerance range. The system will shut down and power off if shutdown is enabled.

sc2TrapTempSensorOk.name: sc2TrapTempSensorOk
sc2TrapTempSensorOk.description: The indicated broken temperature sensor is OK again.

sc2TrapTempSensorBroken.name: sc2TrapTempSensorBroken
sc2TrapTempSensorBroken.description: The indicated temperature sensor is broken.

sc2TrapPowerSupplyAdded.name: sc2TrapPowerSupplyAdded
sc2TrapPowerSupplyAdded.description: One hot-replace power supply was added.

sc2TrapPowerSupplyRemoved.name: sc2TrapPowerSupplyRemoved
sc2TrapPowerSupplyRemoved.description: One hot-replace power supply was removed

sc2TrapPowerSupplyCritical.name: sc2TrapPowerSupplyCritical
sc2TrapPowerSupplyCritical.description: Power supply status has become critical.

sc2TrapRedundantPowerSupplyFailed.name: sc2TrapRedundantPowerSupplyFailed
sc2TrapRedundantPowerSupplyFailed.description: One redundant hot-replace power supply failed

sc2TrapPowerSupplyRedundancyLost.name: sc2TrapPowerSupplyRedundancyLost
sc2TrapPowerSupplyRedundancyLost.description: Power supply redundancy no longer available.

sc2TrapPowerSupplyFanFailurePrediction.name: sc2TrapPowerSupplyFanFailurePrediction
sc2TrapPowerSupplyFanFailurePrediction.description: Fan failure prediction in power supply.

sc2TrapAcFail.name: sc2TrapAcFail
sc2TrapAcFail.description: Mains failed in the specified cabinet. This trap can only happen in storage extension cabinets without UPS or BBU. A server will not have time to send this trap.

sc2TrapDcFail.name: sc2TrapDcFail
sc2TrapDcFail.description: DC power failed in the specified cabinet. This is the result of the system's power-good sensor monitoring. The system may stop when this condition occurs.

sc2TrapOnBattery.name: sc2TrapOnBattery
sc2TrapOnBattery.description: The server is operating on battery power - by UPS or backup battery unit (BBU).

sc2TrapOnMains.name: sc2TrapOnMains
sc2TrapOnMains.description: The mains voltage returned after a power failure.

sc2TrapVoltageOk.name: sc2TrapVoltageOk
sc2TrapVoltageOk.description: Power supply voltage is within normal range again.

sc2TrapVoltageTooLow.name: sc2TrapVoltageTooLow
sc2TrapVoltageTooLow.description: Power supply voltage is too low.

sc2TrapVoltageTooHigh.name: sc2TrapVoltageTooHigh
sc2TrapVoltageTooHigh.description: Power supply voltage is too high.

sc2TrapVoltageFailed.name: sc2TrapVoltageFailed
sc2TrapVoltageFailed.description: Power supply voltage is out of range.

sc2TrapCorrectableMemErrorAddr.name: sc2TrapCorrectableMemErrorAddr
sc2TrapCorrectableMemErrorAddr.description: A correctable memory error at specified address was detected.

sc2TrapUncorrectableMemErrorAddr.name: sc2TrapUncorrectableMemErrorAddr
sc2TrapUncorrectableMemErrorAddr.description: An uncorrectable memory error at specified address was detected.

sc2TrapCorrectableMemErrorBank.name: sc2TrapCorrectableMemErrorBank
sc2TrapCorrectableMemErrorBank.description: A correctable memory error at specified bank was detected.

sc2TrapUncorrectableMemErrorBank.name: sc2TrapUncorrectableMemErrorBank
sc2TrapUncorrectableMemErrorBank.description: An uncorrectable memory error at specified bank was detected.

sc2TrapCorrectableMemErrorModule.name: sc2TrapCorrectableMemErrorModule
sc2TrapCorrectableMemErrorModule.description: A correctable memory error at specified module was detected.

sc2TrapUncorrectableMemErrorModule.name: sc2TrapUncorrectableMemErrorModule
sc2TrapUncorrectableMemErrorModule.description: An uncorrectable memory error at specified module was detected.

sc2TrapCorrectableMemError.name: sc2TrapCorrectableMemError
sc2TrapCorrectableMemError.description: A correctable memory error at unknown location was detected.

sc2TrapUncorrectableMemError.name: sc2TrapUncorrectableMemError
sc2TrapUncorrectableMemError.description: An uncorrectable memory error at unknown location was detected.

sc2TrapMemErrorModulePrefail.name: sc2TrapMemErrorModulePrefail
sc2TrapMemErrorModulePrefail.description: A memory module is predicted to fail (prefailure).

sc2TrapMemErrorModuleReplaced.name: sc2TrapMemErrorModuleReplaced
sc2TrapMemErrorModuleReplaced.description: A memory module had failed and was replaced by a hot-spare module.

sc2TrapMemErrorLoggingDisabled.name: sc2TrapMemErrorLoggingDisabled
sc2TrapMemErrorLoggingDisabled.description: Too many correctable memory errors; logging disabled.

sc2TrapMemErrorAnyModuleReplaced.name: sc2TrapMemErrorAnyModuleReplaced
